title: ArchiCAD 11 Chinese Interactive Training Guide
description: In this Interactive Training Guide you will be provided with step by step instructions to build the Massaro House, using ArchiCAD\&#039;s  BIM  architectural environment, also known as the Virtual Building concept. Frank Lloyd Wright designed this project to accentuate a specific New York island in 1950. The Massaros ran the plans by a Frank Lloyd Wright expert architect, Thomas A. Heinz, AIA, who used ArchiCAD to create the construction documentation based on Wright\&#039;s 5 original pencil drawings. This interactive guide is intended to support your early ArchiCAD experiences.
